title: Shadow Ticket by Thomas Pynchon review – his first novel in 12 years tunes into rising fascism in the US
summary: An 88-year-old author has released a new whodunnit novel set during the Prohibition era. The story includes a mix of clowns, Nazis, and a missing cheese heiress. It's a quirky and adventurous take on a classic mystery genre.

title: The Severed Sun review – folk-horror nightmare that harks back to The Crucible
summary: In Dean Puckett's English chiller, a widow with a dark secret confronts the patriarchal oppression of a religious community. Her struggle highlights the pervasive abuse within the group. The narrative weaves themes of resistance and the fight for autonomy.

title: Deserted islands, seagrass meadows and endless ocean: kayaking in Sweden’s new marine national park
summary: In Nämdöskärgården, part of the Stockholm archipelago, low-impact tourism is promoting awareness of the area's delicate ecology and ocean conservation initiatives. This approach allows visitors to enjoy the natural beauty while supporting sustainable practices. The focus is on fostering appreciation for environmental preservation in the region.

title: Travel FX slow to refund £1,500 after Singapore dollars failed to show
summary: A currency firm required the individual to wait for an investigation by Royal Mail regarding a delivery issue. This delay led the person to purchase another £1,500 worth of currency from a different source. The situation highlights challenges in handling delivery problems with the service provider.
